- load from file

- extra-tab to modify text ( plain editor vs. extended editor )
-- as well should provide line numbers
-- copy left to right / right to left on tab-switch
-- validate on tab-switch



- correct window-size on start
- validate wizard-value when typed
- validate whole file when wizard finished and after load
- check that string-size is not exceeded ( use expandString as much as possible ) 
- root /no-root? / sudo ?
- use automake
- build patch for step-size stuff in crontab: https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=830821

